## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**
- `app/layout.js` - Added Vercel Analytics integration
  - Imported `{ Analytics }` from `@vercel/analytics/next`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component to the root layout body
  
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
  
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency tree

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Analytics documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I:

1. Fetched the latest installation instructions to ensure up-to-date implementation
2. Identified this as a Next.js App Router project (Next.js 16.2.0)
3. Installed the `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
4. Added the Analytics component to the root layout file (`app/layout.js`)
5. Placed the `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag per Next.js App Router best practices

### Framework
- **Framework**: Next.js 16.2.0 (App Router)
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Analytics Package**: @vercel/analytics

### Testing
- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ Linter run completed (pre-existing warnings not related to Analytics changes)
- ✅ No test suite configured (skipped)
- ✅ Dependencies properly installed and lockfile updated

### Next Steps for Deployment

To activate Web Analytics:
1. Deploy this project to Vercel (`vercel deploy`)
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard under Analytics
3. Analytics data will begin collecting once users visit the deployed site

The integration is complete and ready for deployment.
